criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

        1.Provision of informed consent prior to any study specific procedures; 2.18 to 75 years
        old ACS patients, male or female; 3.The angiographic luminal diameter narrowing in any
        non-culprit site is between 40%-70%; 4.statin-naive, defined as receiving no statin therapy
        within 3 months;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Have received statin therapy within 3 months;

          2. The angiographic luminal diameter narrowing in any coronary vessels is more than 70%;

          3. Active liver disease, ALT≥3*ULN;

          4. Renal function damage, CrCl＜30ml/min;

          5. Myopathy;

          6. Pregnancy, lactation female;

          7. Using cyclosporine;

          8. Patients with uncontrolled triglyceride levels TG≥5.65 mmol／L;

          9. Poorly controlled diabetes (HbA1c≥10%）Hypersensitivity to rosuvastatin or any of the
             recipients.
